bib_record.title: -A PRELIMINARY MEASUREMENT OF THE NEUTRON TOTAL CROSS- SECTION OF IRON FROM 24 KEV TO 1000 KEV USING THE HARWELL SYNCHROCYCLOTRON.-

free_txt: THE EFFECTS OF 5 SYSTEMATIC ERRORS HAVE BEEN CONSIDER-
ED AND CORRECTED FOR WHERE POSSIBLE, THEY ARE,
(1) MORE THAN 4 STOP PULSES PER START. (2) DEAD TIME
AFTER A STOP PULSE. (3) BEAM MONITORING. (4) BACK-
11 CM DIAMETER BY 2.5 CM THICK, WITH A PHOTOMULTIPLIER
.NE 104 0.5 MM THICK PLASTIC SCINTILLATOR AS A BEAM
10 PIECES, EACH 10.0 CM LONG, WERE CUT FROM THE IRON
(NATURAL) FOIL 3.0 MM THICK BY 50 MM WIDE, WITH TOTAL
WEIGHT OF 1199.25 G. THESE WERE SANDWICHED TOGETHER TO
GIVE A SAMPLE OF THICKNESS,' 0.2546 FE-ATOM/BARN'.
TOTAL METALLIC IMPURITY LESS THAN 15 PARTS IN 10**6.
.THIS DATA SHOULD NOT BE CONSIDERED AS PRELIMINARY IN
THE USUAL SENSE, BUT NEVERTHELESS USED WITH CARE AS
THE MEASUREMENT WAS CARRIED THROUGH MAINLY TO TEST THE
.COMPARISON WITH OTHER MEASUREMENT SUCH AS RPI LINAC,
